P(A)=\frac1{10,000}
P(B)
P(!B|A)=\frac1{100}
P(B|!A)=\frac1{1000}
P(B|A)=\frac{999}{1000}
P(!B|!A)=\frac{99}{100}
P(B)=P(B\cap!A)+P(B\cap A)=P(B|!A)P(!A)+P(B|A)P(A)=
(\frac1{1000})(\frac{9,999}{10,000})+(\frac{999}{1000})(\frac{1}{10,000})=\frac{9,999}{10,000,000}+\frac{999}{10,000,000}
=\frac{10,998}{10,000,000}
P(!A|B)=\frac{P(B|!A)P(!A)}{P(B)}=\frac{(\frac1{1000})(\frac{9,999}{10,000})}{\frac{10,998}{10,000,000}}=(\frac{9,999}{10,000,000})(\frac{10,000,000}{10,998})
=\frac{9,999}{10,998}
